<p class="Body-P"><span class="Body-C">Laptop Purposes and Benefits</span></p>
<p class="Body-P"><span class="Body-C0"> The purpose of the BYU&ndash;Idaho Laptop Initiative is to increase the quality of the     student experience. Students will be equipped with better tools to learn, organize,     communicate, and complete assignments. In addition, long term, expenses will be reduced     as students gain access to less expensive learning material. By incorporating the     laptop initiative into the BYU&ndash;Idaho educational experience, students will be better     prepared for lifelong learning and employment in the information age.</span></p>
<p class="Body-P"><span class="Body-C">Key benefits:</span></p>
<ol class="Body-P0">
<li class="Body-P1"><span class="Body-C0">Improves the ability of students to implement the Learning Model by coming prepared         to class having read about and researched learning objectives available online.</span></li>
<li class="Body-P1"><span class="Body-C0">Enhances the ability of students to make the best use of their time by allowing access         to Internet-based assignments, I-Learn, and other resources between classes, while         they&rsquo;re on campus. Wireless Internet access is available in all campus buildings.</span></li>
<li class="Body-P1"><span class="Body-C0">Allows students to add the laptop purchase expense to the total cost of an education         for federal financial aid and tax refund purposes. </span></li>
<li class="Body-P1"><span class="Body-C0">Provides access to specialized software otherwise available only in on-campus labs.         This software includes programs for computer-aided design and scientific analysis.         If more students utilize this software on laptops, the number of computer labs can         be reduced freeing space for more classrooms. Such flexibility will allow the university         to serve more students.</span></li>
<li class="Body-P1"><span class="Body-C0">Provides easy access to wireless printing from a campus printer: www.byui.edu/wireless/printing.htm         .</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="Body-P"><span class="Body-C0">For more information from the Computer Help Desk, please go to www.byui.edu/helpdesk,     or call (208) 496-9000.</span></p>
